commit.message:
Fix issue #810 in BLSTM to give lstm_h0_reshaped_expanded unique name (#843)

* Update op_mapping.py to fix #810

As discussed in issue  #810 , _lstm_h0_reshaped_expanded name is generated twice with 2 lanes of BLSTM.
Hence, we need to make those names unique. Adding a 'random' prefix is possible but over the top.
Adding the input name from the layer works but verbose.
Hence, using the number of layers as unique position in the builder and graph is accurate and concise.
Here a tentative fix #810
Updated testcase in issue #810

* Corrected small typo

* Changed patch to expand initial_h and initial_c just once

* Typo

* Added test case Torch TestStackedBLSTM()

* - Updated torch test case TestStackedBLSTM() for GitHub issue #810
- Updated op_mapping.py again to use unique names

commit.message:
Remove sync_gitlab_with_github from master (#808)

Because the sync job was showing up as the commit status for every
commit in master, we need to run the scheduled pipeline from a different
branch. Future PRs to modify sync_gitlab_with_github scripts or build
configuration should point to the branch `sync_gitlab_with_github` where
it is maintained separately.

In that branch, the scripts and CI config have been updated such that
they now work (using SSH keys injected via CI variables). Only scheduled
jobs from that branch will have access to those keys.

commit.message:
Enable scheduled CI job to sync Gitlab CI (#806)

* Adds a new CI job, sync_gitlab_with_github, to run the corresponding
  script. This is intended to be used on a schedule and will only run on
  scheduled pipelines.
* Tells all other jobs to _not_ run on scheduled pipelines, so we can
  have a totally separate CI job that just updates Gitlab on a schedule
  without building the rest of the repo.

commit.message:
Add a script to sync PRs to Gitlab for CI (#799)

The current CI setup only seems to kick off builds for commits that have
been pushed to either a branch on apple/coremltools on GitHub, or a
branch on zach_nation/coremltools on Gitlab. This script will enumerate
all of the open PRs on GitHub apple/coremltools, and push their commits
to a corresponding branch on zach_nation/coremltools.

Requires a valid GitHub access token to be set as an environment
variable. This is to use the GitHub API, but it doesn't need any access
beyond PRs on public repos.

Requires push access to zach_nation/coremltools. Only zach_nation can
give you this.
